answers.answer: I don't think that is diabetes or symptoms of diabetes.  The symptoms of diabetes are:Frequent urinationExcessive thirstExtreme hungerUnusual weight lossIncreased fatigueIrritabilityBlurry visionMaybe you should go to a neurologist, a doctor who deals with things involving your head/brain.  Or maybe an ear, nose and throat doctor,  maybe it has something to do with your sinuses or some other thing with your nasal cavity, since it is so close to the eyes.
It sounds like you may have  a serious problem get a cat scan to determine the problem if it persist.
